  "sample_tex": "\\begin{abstract}\nA logistic-regression classifier trained on CSD features (response variance,\nJaccard similarity coefficient, and disagreement rate) achieves\nleave-one-pair-out F1$\\,{=}\\,$0.814 (AUROC$\\,{=}\\,$0.897) for predicting\nboundary proximity, outperforming the best single-indicator baseline by\n16.38\\%, at zero additional API cost.\n\\end{abstract}\n\n\\section{Introduction}\nOur CSD classifier achieves LOPO F1 of 0.814, representing a 16.38\\%\nimprovement over the variance-only baseline (F1=0.699). The disagreement-only\nbaseline achieves F1=0.684. Precision is 0.786 and recall is 0.880 under LOPO\nvalidation. We evaluate N=40 model-task pairs across 5 difficulty levels with\n200 responses per configuration.\n\n\\section{SC3: Classifier Comparison}\nTable 1 shows our best method achieves LOPO F1=0.949 and AUROC=0.996.\nThe CSD approach with task-normalized features outperforms SPUQ by 33.23\\%.\nThe SPUQ baseline required 1520 additional API calls at a cost of $0.45.\nResults with F1=0.949 [0.940, 0.947] demonstrate strong performance.\nThe improvement of 33.2\\% [22.4\\%, 26.2\\%] is statistically significant.",
